## 🐛 Bug Report

I am trying to read some images from excel file, I need co-ordinates data as well, so tried using `getImages()` function to get co-ordinates and then searched for the image file into media array but `getImages()` returns 0 when the xlsx file is created using MS Excel, it works on Google sheets file.

Lib version: `"exceljs": "^4.4.0"`

## Steps To Reproduce

```
const workbook = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
await workbook.xlsx.load(req.file.buffer);

const worksheet = workbook.worksheets[0];

for (const image of worksheet1.getImages()) {
        const img = ( workbook1.model.media ).find((m) => m.index === image.imageId);
        const rowIndex = image.range.tl.nativeRow - 1;
        const columnIndex = image.range.tl.nativeCol;
       //process img file
}
```

## The expected behaviour:

My excel file contains text and images data, I want to read images, push them to S3, then store their URLs along with other text data of their respective rows.
It works perfectly fine when my xlsx file is built using Google Sheet but it fails to detect images when the xlsx file is built using MS excel, maybe any version issue or anything.
Additionally, in case of MS excel as well, images are there in media array, just they're not fetched by `getImages()`


## Possible solution (optional, but very helpful):

In case we don't need co-ordinates, we can use media array but we need the co-ordinates here. if I want to process the images all in order, sometimes they lose the order so we lose all the meaning.

If anyone can suggest any approach, it'll be really helpful, I have so much of data in xlsx file, I can't migrate to google sheets, even if I import this file to sheets, images are lost there.

thank you.
